               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0091AQM">ʾAgarhǝse ʾAbuna Māmās</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1750" notAfter="1800">According to Additio 2, the Ms. was
                        written in the time of King Takla Giyorgis (r. several periods between
                        1779-1800) and "prince" (masfǝn) Walda Lǝʿul (d. 1767?).</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>The owner/donor Tasfā Ṣǝyon is mentioned in the supplication
                     formulas throughout the Ms., as well as his wife Walatta Mikāʾel and his mother
                     Walatta Libānos. Occasionally their names were erased and replaced with that of
                     Walda Lǝʿul (e.g., <locus target="#27ra">27ra</locus>, 31vb, 33rb,
                     37ra).</provenance>
               </history>
               
